'''Mohamed Koné''' (born 7 March 2002) is an Ivorian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for Belgian club [[Royal Charleroi S.C.|Charleroi]] and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].

== Club career ==
A youth product of [[US Torcy|Torcy]], Koné transferred to [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]] in 2020 and began playing with their reserves.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://actu.fr/sports/football/seine-et-marne-de-nombreux-jeunes-talents-au-poste-de-gardiens-de-but_46087181.html|title=Seine-et-Marne. De nombreux jeunes talents au poste de gardiens de but|date=29 October 2021|website=actu.fr|access-date=4 June 2024|archive-date=4 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240604132621/https://actu.fr/sports/football/seine-et-marne-de-nombreux-jeunes-talents-au-poste-de-gardiens-de-but_46087181.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He made appearances on the bench for the senior team in 2021, and on 1 July 2022 signed a 3-year professional contract with the club.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://www.linfodrome.com/sport/78592-football-mohamed-kone-gardien-international-ivoirien-signe-son-premier-contrat-professionnel|title=Football : Mohamed Koné, gardien international ivoirien, signe son premier contrat professionnel|first=Alex K.|last=PAYNE|date=1 July 2022|website=www.linfodrome.com}}</ref> He made his senior and professional debut with the senior Le Havre side in a 2–1 [[Coupe de la Ligue]] win over [[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]] on 7 January 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.footnormand.fr/actualites/sm-caen/le-hac-tient-son-rang-et-poursuit-sa-route-contre-un-malherbe-accrocheur-mais-limite/|title=Le HAC tient son rang et poursuit sa route contre un Malherbe accrocheur|date=7 January 2024|access-date=4 June 2024|archive-date=4 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240604132622/https://www.footnormand.fr/actualites/sm-caen/le-hac-tient-son-rang-et-poursuit-sa-route-contre-un-malherbe-accrocheur-mais-limite/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 17 January 2024, he joined [[USL Dunkerque|Dunkerque]] for the second half of the 2023–24 season in the [[Ligue 2]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foot-national.com/ligue-1/havre-en-manque-de-temps-de-jeu-mohamed-kone-va-etre-prete-en-ligue-2-851278|title=Havre : en manque de temps de jeu, Mohamed Koné va être prêté en Ligue 2|date=17 January 2024|website=Foot National|access-date=4 June 2024|archive-date=4 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240604132621/https://www.foot-national.com/ligue-1/havre-en-manque-de-temps-de-jeu-mohamed-kone-va-etre-prete-en-ligue-2-851278|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 2 July 2024, [[Royal Charleroi S.C.|Charleroi]] signed Koné on a three-year deal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sporting-charleroi.be/news/mohamed-kone-est-zebre/|title=Mohamed Koné est zèbre !|date=2 July 2024|website=www.sporting-charleroi.be|access-date=2 July 2024|archive-date=2 July 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240702160853/https://www.sporting-charleroi.be/news/mohamed-kone-est-zebre/|url-status=live}}</ref>

==International career==
In March 2022, Koné received his first call-up to the senior [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paris-normandie.fr/id290787/article/2022-03-24/football-mohamed-kone-de-la-b-du-hac-la-selection-ivoirienne|title=Football : Mohamed Koné, de la « B » du HAC à la sélection ivoirienne|first=David|last=POISNEL|date=24 March 2022|website=Paris-Normandie|access-date=4 June 2024|archive-date=4 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240604132623/https://www.paris-normandie.fr/id290787/article/2022-03-24/football-mohamed-kone-de-la-b-du-hac-la-selection-ivoirienne|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2023, he was called up to the final [[Ivory Coast national under-23 football team|Ivory Coast U23]] squad for the [[2023 Maurice Revello Tournament]].<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1665294725065129984|title=Ivory Coast unveil their squad for the @TournoiMRevello 2023|user=TournoiMRevello|author=[[Maurice Revello Tournament]]|date=4 June 2023}}</ref>

Koné was again called-up for [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] games against [[Sierra Leone national football team|Sierra Leone]] in October 2024, but remained on the bench for both games.

